Important Production Use Cases

Branching Workflows

Most common use case.


---

Cleanup Tasks

Delete temp files

Should execute even after failures.


---

Notification Systems

Send alert regardless of pipeline outcome


---

Important Production Reality

A lot of Airflow debugging becomes:

"Why downstream task did not execute?"

Very often:

trigger rule issue


---

Best Practice

Good

Use explicit trigger rules in:

branching DAGs

final tasks

cleanup tasks



---

Bad

Relying blindly on:

default all_success

in complex workflows.


---

Important Understanding

Trigger rules evaluate:

upstream task states


They do NOT evaluate:

business logic

data correctness



